    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-10-04T06:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-10-04T06:16:00-05:00" n="568"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d568">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">871.6363/228: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Riggs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-10-04T13:00:00+01:44">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 4, 1924—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>65. Referring to the Department’s number 34, July 30, 5 p.m., paragraph 7.<note
                        n="63" xml:id="d568fn63">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_626">p. 626</ref>.</note> Have
                    today received confirmation through banks and <pb facs="0753" n="659"
                        xml:id="pg_659"/> informed at Ministry Justice of press reports that the
                    Term of Grace Law was extended on the second instant for three months from
                    September 15th, date of its last expiration. Please inform Department of
                    Commerce.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Riggs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
